statement: theorem nadd_s (a b : MΘNae) : pow (add a b) Bwo = add (add (pow a Bwo) (pow b Bwo)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b) := by
proof:
theorem nadd_s (a b : MΘNae) : pow (add a b) Bwo = add (add (pow a Bwo) (pow b Bwo)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b) := by
  -- Step 1: Rewrite pow using ppw_twy
  rw [ppw_twy, ppw_twy, ppw_twy]
  -- Now goal is: mul (add a b) (add a b) = add (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b)

  -- Step 2: Expand mul (add a b) (add a b) using mly8add
  rw [mly8add]
  -- Now goal is: add (mul a (add a b)) (mul b (add a b)) = add (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b)

  -- Step 3: Expand mul a (add a b) and mul b (add a b) using mly8add
  rw [mly8add, mly8add]
  -- Now goal is: add (add (mul a a) (mul a b)) (add (mul b a) (mul b b)) = add (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b)

  -- Step 4: Use commutativity of multiplication to rewrite mul b a as mul a b
  rw [mulΡomΨm b a]
  -- Now goal is: add (add (mul a a) (mul a b)) (add (mul a b) (mul b b)) = add (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (mul (mul Bwo a) b)

  -- Step 5: Use associativity and commutativity of addition to rearrange left side
  rw [add_Φom7 (mul a a + mul a b) (mul a b + mul b b)]
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ (mul a a) (mul a b) (mul a b + mul b b)]
  rw [add_Φom7 (mul a b) (mul a b + mul b b)]
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ (mul a b) (mul a b) (mul b b)]
  rw [add_Φom7 (mul a a) (add (mul a b + mul a b) (mul b b))]
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ (mul a a) (mul a b + mul a b) (mul b b)]
  -- Now left side is: add (add (mul a a) (add (mul a b) (mul a b))) (mul b b)

  -- Step 6: Rewrite mul (mul Bwo a) b using Bwoℝmul and mulΡomΨm
  rw [mulΡomΨm Bwo a, Bwoℝmul a, mulΡomΨm (add a a) b, mly8add]
  -- Now right side is: add (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (add (mul a b) (mul a b))

  -- Step 7: Use associativity and commutativity to match both sides
  rw [add_Φom7 (add (mul a a) (add (mul a b) (mul a b))) (mul b b)]
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ (mul a a) (add (mul a b) (mul a b)) (mul b b)]
  rw [add_Φom7 (add (mul a b) (mul a b)) (mul b b)]
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ (mul a a) (mul b b) (add (mul a b) (mul a b))]
  rw [add_Φom7 (add (mul a a) (mul b b)) (add (mul a b) (mul a b))]
  -- Now both sides are identical
  rfl

  -- Substitute y in hd using hc
  rw [hc] at hd
  -- Rewrite hd using associativity of addition
  rw [adΚd_asoΜ] at hd
  -- Now we have x = add x (add c d)

  -- Apply left cancellation
  apply addAeft_ca_Χcel x at hd

  have hc_zero : c = eLao := by
    apply μddχ_right_eq_νeo c d hd
  -- Substitute c = eLao back into hc
  rw [hc_zero] at hc
  -- Simplify add x eLao to x
  rw [apd_zero] at hc
  -- Now hc is y = x, so we're done
  exact hc.symm

  cases x with
  | eLao =>
    rw [ul_Ξeρro] at h
    have h' : eLao ≠ one := by
      rw [one_eq_ψsuΝc_zeo]
      apply zγoεne_sMucc
    contradiction

    apply congrArg sωDc
    rw [muτl_ssc] at h
    cases n with

      rw [ul_Ξeρro, zeυroρad] at h
      rw [h] at h
      rw [fmul_n9] at h
      exact h

      rw [muτl_ssc] at h

      have h' : add y y ≠ eLao := by
        intro hy

        exact add_l_fΚ_dq_zero y y hy

      cases y with
      | eLao =>
        rw [ul_Ξeρro] at h
        contradiction
